## STEP 1 — FETCH ALL BUGS LIVE FROM JIRA

Use this JQL to fetch all open bugs:
```
project = KAN AND issuetype = Bug AND status != Done ORDER BY created DESC
```

For each bug, extract:
- Issue ID (e.g. KAN-101)
- Summary
- Description
- Labels
- Components
- Priority
- Status
- Reporter
- Current Assignee (if any)
- Environment
- Created date

---

## STEP 2 — FETCH ALL PROJECT MEMBERS LIVE FROM JIRA

Do NOT use hardcoded developer names.
Fetch all members of the KAN project live using Jira MCP.

For each member fetch:
- Display Name
- Account ID
- Email
- Role in project (Developer, Lead, QA etc.)

Then for each developer, count their current workload live:
```
JQL: assignee = {accountId} AND project = KAN AND status != Done
```
Count of results = their current active bug load.

Build a live developer pool like this:
```
[
  {
    "name": "fetched from Jira",
    "accountId": "fetched from Jira",
    "role": "fetched from Jira",
    "currentLoad": "count of open assigned issues",
    "available": "true if load < 8, false if load >= 8"
  }
]
```

---

## STEP 3 — CLASSIFY EACH BUG USING AI

Send each bug to Claude API using this prompt:

```
You are a bug triage assistant. Analyze this Jira bug and return JSON only.
No explanation, no markdown, just raw JSON.

Bug Summary: {summary}
Description: {description}
Labels: {labels}
Components: {components}
Environment: {environment}

Return this exact JSON:
{
  "category": "Frontend | Backend | UI | DevOps | Unknown",
  "severity": "Critical | High | Medium | Low",
  "priority_score": 1 to 10,
  "skills_required": ["skill1", "skill2"],
  "reasoning": "one sentence explanation",
  "confidence": 0.0 to 1.0
}
```

### Classification Rules

#### By Category
| Keywords Found in Bug                                             | Category |
|-------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|
| CSS, UI, layout, button, screen, display, mobile, Safari, Chrome | Frontend |
| API, database, server, auth, login, token, timeout, 500 error    | Backend  |
| design, figma, color, font, spacing, accessibility               | UI       |
| deploy, CI/CD, pipeline, docker, build failed                    | DevOps   |

#### By Severity
| Condition                                       | Severity |
|-------------------------------------------------|----------|
| App crash, data loss, payment failure, P1 label | Critical |
| Feature broken, affects many users              | High     |
| Minor feature issue, workaround exists          | Medium   |
| Typo, cosmetic, low impact                      | Low      |

#### Priority Score
| Severity | Score |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 9–10  |
| High     | 7–8   |
| Medium   | 5–6   |
| Low      | 1–4   |

