## STEP 4 — MATCH BUG TO DEVELOPER

Use the live developer pool from Step 2 and classification from Step 3.

### Match Logic
```
1. Get category from AI classification (Frontend / Backend / UI / DevOps)
2. Read skills.md → get skills list for that category
3. From live developer pool → filter by matching role
4. Among matched role developers → filter by available = true (load < 8)
5. Among available → sort by currentLoad ascending
6. Assign to developer with lowest load
```

### Fallback Logic
```
Primary   → Exact role match + available + lowest load
Fallback1 → Any role + skill keyword match + available
Fallback2 → Any available developer in project
Fallback3 → No one available → label "needs-manual-triage" + notify lead
```

---

## STEP 5 — CONFIDENCE THRESHOLDS

| Confidence    | Action                                        |
|---------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| 85% or above  | Auto-assign directly in Jira                  |
| 65% to 84%    | Suggest assignment, wait for lead approval    |
| Below 65%     | Flag with label "needs-manual-triage"         |

